The paper proposes a framework for graph embedding, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. The focus is on unifying past algorithms and proposing a new algorithm that outperforms state-of-the-art methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, since the paper does not explicitly mention control systems, we rank cs.SD lower on the list.
